cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper focuses on the analysis and design of Raptor codes, which are a type of error-correcting code used in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): Raptor codes are commonly used in network coding, which falls under the networking and internet architecture sub-category. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper discusses joint decoding of Raptor codes, which can be applied in social and information networks. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes an efficient Raptor code design method, which involves optimization and can be considered a data structure and algorithm problem. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper considers performance-complexity trade-offs of Raptor codes, which can be related to computational complexity.
